# 0.45 x 0.45 SINGLE-SIDED directional sign quad. Front face (normal +X) carries
# the textured symbol; the generator yaws the board by heading+pi so this +X face
# aims at the approaching car (-X), un-mirrored. The back face (normal -X) uses a
# PLAIN GRAY material (no texture), so the symbol is readable ONLY from the front.
# This stops the VLM reading a sign from behind / across the U-turn infield
# (cross-loop misreads -- see docs/vlm_sign_phase1_results.md finding 2).
mtllib sign.mtl
v 0 -0.225  0.225
v 0  0.225  0.225
v 0  0.225 -0.225
v 0 -0.225 -0.225
vt 0 1
vt 1 1
vt 1 0
vt 0 0
vn  1 0 0
vn -1 0 0
usemtl sign
f 4/4/1 3/3/1 2/2/1 1/1/1
usemtl back
f 1/1/2 2/2/2 3/3/2 4/4/2
